snippet.textDisplay: Firstly thank you so much for the amazing support making this dream project possible! Yes Part 5 marks the end of this Chapter of the Astartes project. What comes next? snippet.textDisplay: Like many others, I just wanted to add my voice to the many and say wholeheartedly that this art that you have created is without a doubt a complete masterpiece, capturing the look and feel of the WH40K universe in a way that so many others have attempted. This is perfect in every way. I sincerely hope that you continue to work on your passion and produce further works - what you're doing has touched the lives of millions of people and not over some sort of world event or celebrity-centric trash, but with a terrifying vision of a future for humanity painted in clear, strong visuals that transcend even language. You are incredible, and I thank you for taking the time and effort to make these :)

snippet.textDisplay:
The Astartes was sent to capture the 3rd sphere (2 of them are shown where we get introduced to the inquisitor. These Spheres contain an entity known as the Yu'Vath, a warp tainted Xenos race who like to subjugate other races to do their bidding just like the enslaves. Before the inquisitor gets possessed, the 3 spheres begin to talk and one suggest to "break its seal and return [home]". The other Yu'Vath replies that "we will never survive", meaning going into the warp to go home, since they are just living things using the warp, not beings of the warp. The 1st sphere tells the other one to take the astartes with it. So it does, whoever in the warp, the shadowy daemon entities attacked the Yu'Vath, being an entity with great psychic power it lid up the warp like the Eiffel Tower and killed it, severing the ties with the marines, thus they re-enter reality on a probably once Yu'Vath shield world. The distant flashes in the background are the other marines re-entering realspace. The details in this Part five and the series in general is absolutely amazing.

Im doing a story summary video on the Astartes series, in your honor good Sir, may the God Emperor protect you

So, let me see if I have this right...

The Uprising was caused by the followers of C'tan.

That orb thingy is one of the shards.

That huge body is either one of the "gold men" from the lore. Or they be building a new body for the C'tan. Or both.

The Inquisitior is a certified badass, linking himself up to a C'tan like that.

When he warns the Astartes Captain, the C'tan slips through his defences.

They try to warn the strike team. They heard the warning, but it is too late.

The shard takes them.

The Astartes cruiser destroys the captured ship, and the shard with it (the tentacle thing gets blown away).

The main guy ends up on a Necrontyr world.

And the thing is huge. Bigger than it first seems. Those small cylindrical shapes are huge ass pillars and the rest of the team is teleported in.

snippet.textDisplay:
Here are my thoughts, after watching most of the reaction videos' analysis and reading several reddit posts/youtube comments:


Part 1-4:
The astartes kill team(our 5 man squad) were launched out of a cobra destroyer inside of a caestus assault ram, backed by 2 remotely/servitor-piloted "drones" and a thunderbolt fighter.
The boarding action went smoothly with the kill team successfully landing on the rebel ship and killing the entire crew.
The rebel planetary defense force was lightly armored and had autoguns, lasguns, a missile launcher, and a mobile dual-linked multilaser. Nothing the marines couldn't easily handle.
The 2 augmented rebels guarding the vault were the last of the rebels to be killed. They were likely not human at all, but more like miniatures of the golden body seen inside the vault, which had huge cables coming out of the back of its head and a missing hand, much like these two psychic guards. No blood was seen on the combat knife and, upon falling to the ground, they made a very heavy, metallic thud. They were likely created by the rebels under the guidance of the orb, with many more of those psychic masks being seen around the golden body. It is unclear if they were directly controlled by the orb or not. Though it can be noted the orb's energy from 2:43-2:50 is similar to what's seen in the psychic rebel's eyes in part 4 at 0:58.


Part 5:
(0:14-0:24) The command team(our veteran sergeant and beaky boi) was overseeing the operation through helmet cam on-board a nova frigate, backed by a dauntless cruiser.
Servitors(or serfs) can be seen at the consoles of the operations command room. The helmet cam and the inquisitorial psyker were both being monitored here.


(0:25-1:05) In another chamber, with many purity seals, wards, and incense posted up outside, were the captive orbs. The one in clear focus is bound and chained in a sort of cage; the pumping nodes on its surface seem to be inhibiting its activity. Another orb can be seen in the same type of cage in the back towards the right, though it was likely dead/inactive.
The inquisitorial psyker is hooked up to the living orb and seems to have been monitoring it for a long time. He is in prayer and burning incense.


(1:15-1:27) As the kill team enters the vault, it is clear temperatures are freezing as ice cracks at the astartes' feet and their power armors' exhaust is creating steam. Low temperatures are a sign warp activity is nearby.


(1:43-2:01) The kill team passes the golden body and the psychic masks. They pay little attention, like they already know what all this is. It seems like either the golden body was being constructed to form a larger variant of the prior 2 psykers OR it was being deconstructed to form those psykers, though this is all speculation and completely unclear at the moment.


(2:06-3:37) They arrive at the orb on-board the rebel ship, which has been influencing and controlling the rebels to do its bidding. It immediately tries to repel the astartes but fails to affect them in any considerable way. The kill team nonchalantly advances through the orb's psychic defenses and proceeds to install transmitters on it. It is pretty clear that these transmitters are directly linking this orb to the one on the frigate.


(3:39-4:59) After the transmitters were installed on the new orb(orb 2), the psychic inhibiting contraption on the captive orb(orb 1) was deactivated, allowing orb 1 to awaken and initiate communications with orb 2. The inquisitorial psyker is able to eavesdrop on their conversation, catching this:

orb 1: Who is here?
orb 2: I have failed, brother. We have all failed.
orb 1: The astartes deny our touch. You must return. Break your seal.
orb 2: That's impossible. We'll never survive.
orb 1: You must. Take the alpha.
Inquisitorial psyker: Return them immediately!



The psyker removes his attention from the orbs to warn the veteran sergeant, who calls for the kill team's extraction. Unfortunately, this gave an opening for orb 1 to attack him.


orb 1: At last, you are mine.


The orb then overloads both the psychic inhibitors and the psyker. At this point, the psyker is still battling the orb, but it quickly becomes a losing battle.


Inquisitorial psyker: Go. It is taking hold, but, remember, he said that the warp tainted would receive the emperor's hand.
Possessed psyker: Ji no cressell.


The psyker seems to lose all control and is exposed to raw warp energy(the blue light). The veterans spare no time in removing the danger.


(5:02-5:55) The kill team is still standing by awaiting further orders, next to orb 2.
The squad sergeant receives some vox comms and replies:


Sergeant: Did we do something?! No!


It is unclear what he was being told. Then orb 1 says "Cressell", reveals its hidden form, and begins absorbing the entire squad. It can be noted that since the squad might be under a strict no-touch policy, the marine to the left of the sergeant appears to aim his boltgun at the sergeant when his hand was pulled into the orb. This isn't super clear but it is likely due to how seriously they take the risk of corruption. As the sergeant's hand was being absorbed, orb 1 says "I takanah" and moving markings/inscriptions start appearing on his gauntlet. Also worth noting is how the marines were being pulled to the orb; it is as if the tentacles of the creature were reaching out and grabbing their individual limbs, but it can't be seen in the material world due to its nature of being a warp-being. When the sergeant fires off the plasma pistol, the tentacle holding his right hand(now nonexistent) releases it and his arm was allowed to swing backwards.


(6:02-6:17) Now in the warp, the creature in orb 1 can be seen holding the entire squad in its tentacles. This moment is very brief(or not because time doesn't exist in the warp) before something destroys the creature, releasing the squad.


(6:18-6:57) Our kill team is teleported to this world. Each marine is teleported on top of a different pillar(we only see 3 flashes but can assume all of them made it). The coagulated blood is due to the larraman's cells doing their work of keeping the astartes' bleeding down to a minimal. It seems a bit of the black carapace can be seen on the back of the sergeant's head. The 3 studs above the brow indicate 3 centuries of service.


Teaser:
(7:13-7:19) It looks like this marine is in battle with dark eldar, who've fired splinter weaponry at the marine. A predator tank pulls up behind the marines, dispensing the emperor's will.


Quick points:
-It is clear that there are 3 orbs, 2 on the command ship and 1 on the rebel ship.
-It is clear the Retributors knew what they getting into and what they were fighting. Perhaps they were not expecting the psyker to lose control(they gave him plenty of time to demonstrate control... or the lack of it) but they were definitely prepared for it.
-The creator seems to have stated that the orbs are a homebrew enemy, an amalgam of several existing 40K ideas and his own imagination.
-The creator has also stated they are not fighting Chaos
-A lot is still unclear until the creator can provide some clarity
-This entire series has been SICK. Please support the creator on his patreon. Also take a look at Mark Louis Spark's Death of Hope if you haven't yet.
